What is soundless, touchless, formless, imperishable, tasteless,
constant, odorless, without beginning, without end, higher than the
great, unchanging --

By discerning That, one is liberated from the mouth of death. ... If
one recites this supreme secret in an assembly of Brahmans, or at a
time of the ceremony for the dead, devoutly --

That makes for immortality.
